heading_context: Appeal a penalty for filing your company accounts late
chunks.html_content: Use this service to appeal a penalty from Companies House for filing a company’s annual accounts late.
chunks.plain_content:
Appeal a penalty for filing your company accounts late
Use this service to appeal a penalty from Companies House for filing a company’s annual accounts late.

heading_context: Appeal a penalty for filing your company accounts late
chunks.html_content: You should pay the late filing penalty even if you want to appeal, unless there are exceptional reasons, such as a fire destroying records.
chunks.plain_content:
Appeal a penalty for filing your company accounts late
You should pay the late filing penalty even if you want to appeal, unless there are exceptional reasons, such as a fire destroying records.

heading_context: Appeal a penalty for filing your company accounts late
Before you start
chunks.html_content:
You’ll need:

  • the company number
  • the penalty reference
  • the reason for the appeal
  • any documents that support the appeal

Any documents you upload, such as a doctor’s note or an insurance claim, must include:

  • the full name of the person or company affected
  • any relevant dates

The maximum file size for each document is 4MB.

heading_context: Appeal a penalty for filing your company accounts late
After you appeal
chunks.html_content:
Wait for Companies House to contact you with their decision.

If you have not paid the penalty, you may be contacted by a debt recovery agency or solicitors asking for payment. Reply to them explaining you have appealed the penalty.

Other ways to appeal
Appeal by email
chunks.html_content:
You can also appeal a penalty by email or post.

Send your email with any supporting evidence attached to Companies House.
